  "prompt": "What is the economic system of Pakistan? How long has this been the system?",
  "response": "Pakistan has a mixed economy, which incorporates elements of both capitalism and socialism. In this system, both the private sector and the government play significant roles in economic activities. The government maintains control over certain key industries such as defense, electricity, and infrastructure, while the private sector is predominant in agriculture, manufacturing, services, and other industries.\n\nThe mixed economic system has been in place since Pakistan's independence in 1947, although the balance between government control and private enterprise has fluctuated over time. Different governments have introduced varying degrees of state intervention and privatization policies depending on their economic philosophies and the challenges they faced. Over the decades, Pakistan has gone through phases of nationalization (particularly in the 1970s) and periods of liberalization and privatization (notably starting in the late 1980s and 1990s). The system continues to evolve with changing political and economic circumstances.",
